From: 4noha
Subject: bcmbt_fdt: extend post-firmware HCI reset delay from 250ms to 2s
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

DM250 (AP6212A / Broadcom BCM43430) cannot complete post-firmware HCI
Reset within the upstream 250ms window. Extend the post-firmware quiet
period to 2s so the chip is reachable when bcmbt_fdt proceeds to
bcmbt_uart_init() / HCI Reset.

Note: this patch alone is NOT sufficient to drive BT bring-up to
completion on every DM250 unit observed (see kernel-patches/README.md
"Status" column). It is, however, the minimal change that unblocks the
2026-05-29 successful bring-up captured in the prebuilt kernel
`bsd.armv7.delay-2s` (see prebuilt-info/).

--- sys/dev/fdt/bcmbt_fdt.c.orig	Fri May 29 12:29:01 2026
+++ sys/dev/fdt/bcmbt_fdt.c	Fri May 29 12:29:53 2026
@@ -205,7 +205,7 @@
 	free(fw, M_DEVBUF, fwlen);

 	/* wait for chip reset after firmware download */
-	delay(250000);
+	delay(2000000); /* DM250 patch: 250ms was insufficient */

 	/* re-initialize UART after chip reset */
 	if (bcmbt_uart_init(sc, 115200) != 0) {
